Car insurance, which covers the driver in the face of potential damage, involves a significant expenditure that will depend on various factors, such as age, sex, anticipation of the driving licence, the civil condition, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use of it, among other things.
To have a car is the main one.
It is that, escoger el seguro de automóvil adecuado es incluso más difícil que elegir el modelo de vehículo.
And it is that, choosing the proper car insurance, is even more difficult than choosing the vehicle model.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insurer.
This compromise is materialized by an insurance contract, which establishes that the company receives the value of the premium granted and in exchange it becomes responsible for the obligation to pay compensation in the event of damage.
The premium is the insurance price, which is based on various factors such as age, sex, antennaity of the driving licence, civil status, type of vehicle to be insured, or use of the vehicle, among other things.
Insurance companies set their prices according to statistics, so that the higher the probability of an accident, the higher the rate to be paid.
For this reason, people over 25 years of age and women must pay lower premiums, as statistics show that these people have a lower rate of harm from caution to caution.
Similarly, using censuses, companies concluded that married persons tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use of the vehicle will affect the frequency, and thus the likelihood of an accident.
By increasing frequency the probability increases.
They are many of the variables that insurers take into account when setting the premium price.
This is why the driver has to study the situation well in order to choose the vehicle insurance that is best suited to his profile.
Here we will present the most significant variables at the time of choosing one type of insurance, so that the insurance company, in addition to adapting to the insurer's characteristics, will offer him a reasonable price.
Young people under 25 years of age have to face various disadvantages when entering an insurance contract at an accessible price, as may be the low experience in driving and driving licences.
Although the ideal to be insured is an insurance at any risk, there are other more economical options.
The most foreseeable drivers can opt for any risk insurance with franchise, so that they obtain insurance cover at any risk but at a more accessible price.
This form of agreement implies that the client pays part of the amount of the damage.
"The part of the amount of damage that the customer will pay will be determined according to the value of the premium, which will be higher the amount will be low," says Luis Noguera, the manager in Spain of First Europa, an online insurance agent.
Another option is extended third-party insurance, so that the customer ensures protection to deal with damage caused to third-party, but by those caused on his own car.
In addition, it would be covered against theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
A advice.
If you are under 25 years of age, you try to be careful and avoid damage as far as possible, as this will affect the benefit, which may reduce the insurance price in the future.
A subsidy is a reduction in the company's basic tariff.
On the contrary, a penalty is an increase in the basic tariff.
"The bonuses and sanctions will depend on the company and its benefit.
If the company had a good year, it could afford to increase bonuses," clarified Noguera.
Beyond 25 years, this becomes easier for drivers when entering into an insurance contract, as the damage rate is reduced thanks to the accumulated experience.
For this reason, it is preferable to choose a risk insurance with franchise.
"Normally, young people cannot benefit from the experience gained in advance after an accident," says the director of the European company in Spain and adds that the majority of accidents occur during the second year of driving, once the 'peace of novice' has passed.
However, if the client is married but has no children yet, it is preferable that he negotiates insurance at any risk as soon as his economic situation allows him.
Marriages with children are considered by insurers as persons with the lowest rate of damage, because increases will be lower.
